The paper discusses computational models of object recognition, specifically in the context of the primate brain's ventral stream. This is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses learning rules and architectures, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the neural tuning of the brain, which is relevant to neuroscience and computational neuroscience (cs.NI).
